Calculate the marginal distribution as follows:(32)Pr{Y=y}=∑x=0∞P(X=x,Y=y)=∑x=0∞P(Y=y∣X=x)P(X=x)=∑x=y∞(xy)(x+n−1x)py(1−p)x−y(1−q)nqx(conditional probability is 0 if y>x)=∑x=y∞x!y!(x−y)!⋅(x+n−1)!x!(n−1)!⋅(n+y−1)!(n+y−1)!py(1−p)x−y(1−q)nqx=∑x=y∞(x+n−1x−y)(n+y−1y)py(1−p)x−y(1−q)nqxqyq−y=(n+y−1y)(pq)y(1−q)n∑x=y∞(x+n−1x−y)((1−p)q)x−y=(n+y−1y)(pq1−q+pq)y(1−q1−q+pq)n. egin{document}$$\displaystyle \Pr ig\{Y = y ig\}&= \sum_{x=0}^{\infty}P(X=x, Y=y) = \sum_{x=0}^{\infty}P(Y=y \mid X=x) P(X=x) 
onumber \ &= \sum_{x=y}^{\infty} inom{x}{y} inom{x+n-1}{x}p^{y} (1-p)^{x-y}(1-q)^{n} q^{x} \quad 	ext{(conditional probability is 0 if }y \gt x	ext{)}
onumber \ &= \sum_{x=y}^{\infty} rac{x!}{y!(x-y)!}\cdot  rac{(x+n-1)!}{x!(n-1)!}\cdot  rac{(n+y-1)!}{(n+y-1)!}p^{y} (1-p)^{x-y}(1-q)^{n} q^{x} 
onumber \ &= \sum_{x=y}^{\infty} inom{x+n-1}{x-y} inom{n+y-1}{y}p^{y} (1-p)^{x-y}(1-q)^{n} q^{x} q^{y} q^{-y}
onumber \ &=  inom{n+y-1}{y}(pq)^{y} (1-q)^{n} \sum_{x=y}^{\infty} inom{x+n-1}{x-y} ig((1-p)q ig)^{x-y}
onumber \ &=  inom{n+y-1}{y}\left( rac{pq}{1-q + pq}ight)^{y} \left( rac{1-q}{1-q + pq}ight)^{n}.$$\end{document}
